## ğŸ”¹ 1. BASIC PLAYWRIGHT QUESTIONS

### Q1. What is Playwright?

**Answer:**
Playwright is an **open-source end-to-end test automation tool** developed by Microsoft. It supports **Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit**, and enables **UI, API, and cross-browser testing** with built-in auto-wait and parallel execution.

---

### Q2. Playwright vs Selenium?

| Playwright                     | Selenium                    |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------- |
| Auto-wait built-in             | Manual waits                |
| Faster execution               | Slower                      |
| Supports API testing           | UI only                     |
| Parallel by default            | Needs setup                 |
| Handles modern web apps better | Struggles with dynamic apps |

---

### Q3. Languages supported by Playwright?

* JavaScript / TypeScript
* Java
* Python
* C#

